meanings: receive protection from people in power[influential people]

vlive.english: he was kind of unlikeable on "Infinity Challenge."

examples.english: The new law will be a charter for unscrupulous financial advisers.

examples.korean: 왕은 기사단의 비호를 받아 피난길에 올랐다.
examples.english: King rose on refuge way under covert to knights.

examples.english: I won't screen you from blame[suspicion].

examples.korean: 그는 테러분자들을 비호할 경우 누구든 테러분자와 마찬가지 취급을 받게 될 것임을 밝혔다고 말합니다.
examples.english: He said, “I laid out a doctrine, and it said: 'If you harbor a terrorist, you're equally as guilty as the terrorists.'
